The paper discusses coordination in distributed systems, which is a topic typically covered in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses temporal ordering requirements and characterizes them in terms of causal communication patterns, which are topics covered in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the analysis of communication patterns, which is a topic covered in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses generic classes of coordination problems, which is a topic covered in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
